pr_title: rgw: add package version support to lua scripting
pr_body:
This patch allows users to set the package version when adding packages
to rgw's luarocks package manager.
Previously, when stating a specific version the package was not found.

Fixes: https://tracker.ceph.com/issues/51193
Signed-off-by: Matan Breizman <Matan.Brz@gmail.com>

> why not just remove all versions of the package in this case - since you do that in line 159 and on?

trying to match `luarocks` behavior, if a version was provided in the removal - only the specific one will be removed. otherwise, all the versions will be removed.
the case where a specific version is provided is between lines 151-157 (ending with `return 0` in order to avoid removing all the other versions).
the latter case is in line 159 and on, removing all versions since no version specification was provided.


', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 6, 28, 18, 53, 9, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Matan-B', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 660374930, 'comment_body': 'please use the shorter format of this code (same as in the add script function)', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 6, 29, 8, 0, 30, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'yuvalif', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 660516971, 'comment_body': '"const"', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 6, 29, 11, 15, 4, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'yuvalif', 'type': 'User'}]

[{'comment_id': 661208498, 'comment_body': 'can we use the `UserMetaTable` instead?
we will have `Request.User` here, and then `User.Id` and `User.Tenant` similar to other places where we have "User"', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 6, 30, 7, 38, 22, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'yuvalif', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 662168846, 'comment_body': '`get_id()` just return a reference to an `rgw_user` object, so this pointer to it cannot be null.

pr_title: rgw: Lua scripting global map feature
pr_body:

Lua script and bind a shared Lua table with a cpp map.

This feature allows users to assign execution context to Lua scripts. The three supported contexts are ``preRequest``" which will execute a script before each
operation is performed, ``postRequest`` which will execute after each operation is performed, and ``background`` which will execute within a specified time interval.
A request context script may be constrained to operations belonging to a specific tenant's users.
The request context script can also access fields in the request and modify some fields. All Lua language features can be used.
```', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 5, 30, 18, 33, 41, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'anthonyeleven', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 885028639, 'comment_body': '* When uploading a script with the \`\`background\`\` context, a tenant name may not be specified.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 5, 30, 18, 34, 37, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'anthonyeleven', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 885029168, 'comment_body': 'The \`\`background\`\` context may be used for purposes that include analytics, monitoring, caching data for other context executions.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 5, 30, 18, 36, 7, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'anthonyeleven', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 885029906, 'comment_body': 'The \`\`RGW\`\` Lua table is accessible from all contexts and saves data written to it
during execution so that it may be read and used later during other executions.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 5, 30, 18, 38, 6, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'anthonyeleven', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 885031275, 'comment_body': '- Each RGW instance has its own private and ephemeral \`\`RGW\`\` Lua table that is lost when the daemon restarts.  Note that \`\`background\`\` context scripts will run on every instance.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 5, 30, 18, 41, 50, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'anthonyeleven', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 885031960, 'comment_body': '- The maximum number of entries in the table is 100,000. Each entry has a key and string value with a combined length of no more than 1KB. A Lua script will abort with an error if the number of entries or entry size exceeds these limits.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 5, 30, 18, 43, 47, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'anthonyeleven', 'type': 'User'}]
